# Vnansial — Super Platform v2 (personal-AI direction)
Priority: P0
Status: in_progress
Last updated: 2026-05-15

## Goal
Turn Vnansial from a multi-tool web app into a **personal financial AI**
that you can run anywhere (Docker / VPS / Telegram) and that does almost
everything from the chat surface.

## Why
The bento web app proved the surface area; now the AI needs the depth to
truly replace 5 apps. The win condition is: "user opens chat, asks for
anything financial, gets a tool-driven answer + chart + persistent
memory."

## Tracks
1. **Visibility** — show the agent's tool calls inline so demo viewers
   understand the autonomy. Already in chat data; needs polish.
2. **Charts in chat & pages** — Yahoo + CoinGecko history rendered as
   SVG/SSR so the AI can include `[[chart:BBCA.JK]]` in replies.
3. **Sessions & memory** — every chat is a row in SQLite, exportable to
   `.md`. Users can have many parallel sessions (per-agent, per-topic).
4. **Multi-agent** — predefined presets (Investor, Pemula, Cek-Penipuan,
   Coach) plus user-defined agents stored in SQLite with custom prompts.
   Active agent is chosen by dropdown.
5. **Settings page** — masked secrets (Telegram token shown as `••••`),
   PIN-gated edits, per-user Telegram chat-id binding.
6. **Number masking** — every currency input shows `1.000.000` not
   `1000000`.
7. **More crypto** — full CoinGecko search (250+ top + on-demand search
   for any meme coin) accessible from page + AI tool.
8. **Alerts + cron** — node-cron driven; price/event/balance alerts
   persisted in SQLite; Telegram & in-app notifications.
9. **CI/CD + container registry** — GitHub Actions builds + pushes to
   `ghcr.io/mukhayyar/vnansial`. Users `docker run` with env override.
10. **Puppeteer fallback for IDX** — optional, env-gated; bypasses
    Cloudflare for emiten detail when JSON endpoints 403.
11. **AI cross-channel** — the same agent reachable in Telegram, web,
    and CLI (`scripts/vnansial-cli.js` future).

## Shipped this iteration (track-by-track)
- Track 1: tool-timeline shown in ChatUI (existing) — polish only
- Track 2: TradingChart component + /api/market/history works; agent
  tool `render_chart` returns chart spec for inline rendering
- Track 3: SQLite `session` + `message` tables, `/api/sessions/*` CRUD,
  client session picker, `.md` export endpoint
- Track 4: `server/agent/presets.js`, SQLite `agent` table, agent
  dropdown in ChatUI, system prompt swap per turn
- Track 5: `/settings` page with masked Telegram, PIN-gated POST
- Track 6: `formatIDR()` + `<MoneyInput>` component applied site-wide
- Track 7: `/api/crypto/search` endpoint via CoinGecko `/search`
- Track 8: `node-cron` + `alert` table + alert CRUD scaffolded (no
  notification daemon yet — flag-gated to ship)
- Track 9: `.github/workflows/release.yml` builds Docker, pushes to ghcr
- Track 10: Puppeteer scaffold + env flag (heavy dep, opt-in only)
- Track 11: agent reachable in Telegram already; CLI deferred

## Roadmap (not in this iteration)
- Inline streaming SSE tool calls
- True multi-agent communication (agent-to-agent handoff with
  scratchpad shared state)
- Push notifications via service worker
- Family / household profiles
- Mobile PWA installer

## How AI agents extend this
See `CLAUDE.md` / `AGENTS.md` — every new domain follows the same recipe
(lib → tool wrapper → definition → endpoint → page).
